            "description": "## Unauthorized Payment Request\n\nThis request tests the **POST /payments** endpoint under an unauthorized access scenario — specifically, when the `Authorization` header is missing or empty.\n\n### Purpose\n\nValidates that the API correctly rejects payment attempts that lack valid authentication credentials, ensuring the endpoint is properly secured against unauthorized access.\n\n### Expected Behavior\n\nThe server should respond with **`401 Unauthorized`**, blocking the payment from being processed.\n\n### Request Body\n\n| Field | Type | Description |\n| --- | --- | --- |\n| `amount` | integer | The payment amount (e.g. `150`) |\n| `currency` | string | Currency code (e.g. `\"CAD\"`) |\n| `payment_method` | string | Payment method type (e.g. `\"card\"`) |\n| `card_number` | string | The card number to charge |\n| `expiry` | string | Card expiry date in `MM/YY` format |\n| `cvv` | string | Card security code |\n\n### Headers\n\n| Header | Value |\n| --- | --- |\n| `Content-Type` | `application/json` |\n| `Authorization` | _(empty — intentionally omitted to trigger 401)_ |\n\n### Post-Response Test\n\nThe following test is run after the response is received to assert the expected 401 status:\n\n``` js\npm.test(\"Unauthorized request blocked\", function() {\n    pm.response.to.have.status(401);\n});\n\n ```"
